sec.p:
The total infant weight, in the vertical direction, has two components, one in the inclined plane, favoring slipping, and one normal to the inclined plane, responsible for the friction force opposing slipping. Calling Wt the total infant weight carried in mounting position, Wc the effective weight limit for clinging, and μ the static friction coefficient (Bowden and Tabor 1956), the equilibrium of forces on the infant requires that force components on the inclined plane direction satisfy the condition:
